Nothing is related to Pazhassi Raja. It’s just a honour to him.

Museum is at east hill which was one of administrative block of British rule in Malabar. Well maintained and guide at museum help us to know the history of all artefacts displayed. No photos allowed. Best for one day trip especially school children.
A nice sport for relaxation and also a heritage place. Alots of things to study and a wonderful experience will get from there. Need to go there

Some interesting artefacts here. But the low budget allocation is obvious. They have done the best they can to maintain the museum, but the lack of resources is a big let down. And the artefacts themselves are nothing to write home about. A few clay pots and weapons catch your attention. 

Visit, if only if you are in the area.

This is located near to Calicut staff over here are not cooperative. you have to keep the exact change in your hand otherwise they will not I love you inside if you don't have change there is no option to enter inside.. card swiping also not available...
Quite informative; came across articles og bygone era. Engrossing. The guide ther, English speaking, trained was quite helpful. Time usefully spent..

One of the famous place in kerala. A lot of people visit the Kozhikode beach. It is one of the most fascinating tourist destination in the district of Kozhikode. It is also one of the busiest places in Kozhikode district. This place is suitable for every of people. Good place. Best place for spending our time. And also for children a park is here.
There are some beautiful modern sculptures.. the beach looks good.. But the northern part of the beach smells bad and it's not that much clean on that side
Good place to hang out. Sunset was awesome. Good  place for every age group. Good location for jogging, running practice and other activities.nice location for click some awesome photos
Super crowded beach with lots of snack option. They have a stage where functions are often happens and they take away the serenity of the beach. Visit in the morning for best experience

Not a pristine beach but you can have fun here , tends to get crowded in the evenings . 
I watched a beautiful sunset . 
There was a lot of street vendors selling all those things nostalgic. 
Vegetables in brine and vinegar is sold by most of the vendors ,  although hygiene is questionable , i still are some .

Good place to learn cool facts about our own solar system. It has made for the studies of the Universe, solar system and stars. It's a cheap and best hangout place for kids and families. There are four Planetarium shows and 3D shows. On special days like lunar or solar eclipse special arrangements are also done by the centre to get a detailed view of the sun and moon. There is kids play area, science activities, mirror mage and scary house in the centre.

A good place to hangout and get some knowledge on science. The place is mostly for kids, especially the 3D show. You can learn some physics here with all the items around. There are also some animals and birds here, who are fun to watch. Overall, I'd say this place is fantastic and great to bring your kids.
Super place.... Good place for school trips... Many science related games , it's very interesting....

Awesome place to spent a few hours in calicut. The place is well maintained. The planetorium show wasn't as good as compared to the one in trivandrum. Overall a very good place to visit with your family especially kids.

Only for kids.
 If you are expecting you can know about star gazing, constellations, and solar system from this planetarium,  planetarium will disappoint you because now the show is a fancy one without much content. Even the 3d show is of low standard, just for kids. People expect more information dissemination from regional science center.

A special place for Shiva devotees. You would feel good once you visit the temple.
Very Old Temple, visit early by 4.30 am, very Positive Energy place

A religious place of historical importance.

 Beautiful & architectural design

14 th century historical mosque and lots to see around , positive vibes all around , it's an another side of calicut , everyone who visit calicut must visit kuttichira

Its a very old architecture and is well maintained! This place also has a water body in front of the masjid which is also a nice place to visit.

A must visit of History Lovers. It is a Symbol of Indo-Arab Trade dating 100s of years. Mosque was built by a Yemani Arab Trader. It is unique in design.
Masha Allah.... My overall experience is good in this mosque.
Vibe area.Old masjid.I like to kittichira

Mishkal Mosque, the four-storied mosque situated in Kuttichira in Kozhikode is built by an Arab trader and ship owner,
Most attractive indo arab architecture and most visited holy place in calicut near beach
There near to it a qasi house were situated and it had been maintained by Kozhikode qasis. Best and attractive one in malabar

The people of this place are just into money making business. I wasn’t knowing they charge 150 bucks as Entry fees which is general entry and 250 bucks for Special entry. I felt like they are more interested in the money than the real prayers. After paying the entry fees they gave me a ticket were few programs were mentioned. After entering, few stops are there where you need to show the tickets and do particular prayings where also the donation boxes were there. You need not to give any donation there out of your will. Yes, if you are willing to then you go ahead. I went in afternoon so the floors were quit hot and because my footwear was kept outside it was very uneasy to walk in few areas. So I suggest better go either in morning time or  in evenings. Anyway the statue of Lord Shiva was worth seeing. And that was the only part I liked after I entered. I would have loved the place if the temple people were not into business and more about holy rituals.

Temple of Lord Shiva. A huge statue of Lord Shiva siting in meditation position is been erect here. Just situated in well approachable location, focuses on all holy location of Lord Shiva and benefits of meditation. One can buy passes for various pooja and attraction.. At last can sit in front of Lord and feel all positive vibes around. Must visit place.

This is good place. But the entry ticket prices are different like 150rs and 250rs. There is a ticket for 50rs. Normal days 50rs ticket and 150rs does not make any difference. Overall good place to visit within city limit but ticket prices are high. Temple closes by 8pm. Peaceful place.

This is good for one time visiting. You will feel good here. However, most commercial temple in the Bangalore. Basically, this is not a temple. Beaware, ask the tickets Rs 50 for entry only. Otherwise they will give you Rs.150 per head. If you are going there for pray purpose.

This temple has turned more into a business than a place of worship. The priests aren't interested in talking/worshiping but offerings. The environment is hardly peaceful. As if the entry ticket of 250/ is not enough, they ask for more money at every stage.

This place passes just about okay for a vegetarian restaurant. I stopped for lunch and found the menu short in variety and average in quality. On the plus side is the convenient location for those who are taking Koyilandy-Ramanattukara bye-pass travelling from North to South. Parking for maybe half a dozen cars at a time.
Nice location.... Good food available.... Best vegetarian food.... good staff service.... Nice dealing
I love this place... good veggie food in south Indian style.. they have changed their old menu but still it's good and tasty
Nice place to have the traditional south style coffee.. A quite and relaxing place by the highway, I tend to return to this place when I crave for a simple but refreshing south Indian breakfast .

I love this place... Visiting this since 2012... Yes.. best things do happen over a cup of coffee...  Lots of memories for lifetime...
A nice place if you want to spend time leisurely. ( without spending too much) Ps: We ordered only a tea and coffee so no comments about the food. Service was fine.

Awesome place to dine. Nice ambience. It seems like we are inside a luxurious airplane or train. Very neat and clean table and utensils. Staffs were courteous and helpful. we had soup, ghee rice etc. And it was great food. The price is reasonable and not very cheap. Ample car parking space available.

Nice ambience and tasty food. The major part of the restaurant was recently closed down for repair. Heard they are opening up soon after renovations. Recommended for a leisurely dinner. Excellent service too. They have variety of cuisine available ready to serve.
Great Malabar cuisine. But if you're not a native (which is in my case) you won't like it very much. Ambiance is good for the place but the staff are little less concerned.

Very tasty food. Service was also good. But there is very less space inside which will be very crowded too. May need to wait for some time to get a vacant seat. You may need to share the table with other people unless you are a group of 4.

Paragon is always one of my all time favourite restaurants. The food and beverages served are of high quality. Rates are reasonable and apt. The quantity of food served is also very good. Also they supply a variety of dishes in all their restaurants and all of them maintain the same quality and standard. The staff are well behaved and polite

It's famous for non-veg dishes. I have been trying different vegetarian dishes from years and observed that the vegetarian food quality degrading. I have seen rats inside the air conditioned section on steps and restroom areas. 

Expecting better quality inside and increased food quality as the price going high so the quality should go high.

Non vegetarian eaters may have different view. Thanks.

Best Biriyaani in the World....!!!!
I like it very much... If you are not tasted it...oh lose... Go and enjoy the taste. My friends are very excited to go there.... Good atmosphere superb facilities. Very neat and clean.... Ample parking space. Anyway good experience.....

Great spot to grab some lunch in the heart of Byron! Right on the beach, great open area undercover and a cute outdoor patio area. Highly recommend checking out this spot. I personally prefer it during the day, it’s not as crowded as it is at night. 
The food is really good too!! Just a tip if you’re traveling and trying to save money.. I ordered from the kids menu and ordered the fish and chips which was a decent amount with a side salad and it was cheaper than the regular fish and chips and just as filling. 
Highly recommend checking out this spot. 
The bar is also amazing. Great beer selection and good mixed drinks.
Retty awesome place to chill, huge beer garden. Constant entertainment. Very lively atmosphere. Awesome music acts and live performances, also you can get a really good feed here as well.

We found this gem while visiting Byron Bay and really enjoyed our stay.  The only reason I'm giving this 4 stars is because the front of the hotel is oddly empty.  It's as if there had been another business in the space and now strange and empty.  The reception is all the in the back and a little tricky to find.  The room was clean and bright with a large balcony facing the pool.  The small kitchenette had a sink chiller, and a kettle with a nice selection of teas.  The pool is very nice and our family enjoyed it since the blue bottles kept us off the beach.
Favourite spot for a Sunday afternoon session. Great food and amazing atmosphere in an amazing location

Spacious bar with a couple of large outdoor areas. Quick service at the bar, nice staff. Big screen in the corner of one of the beer gardens. Great pizza oven fired up ready to cook up a decent pizza in no time.
